                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>schinn wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Ayani wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> So if you give a pet a weapon or item with lots of + Magic Resistance on it, expect more charm breaks!
<br />
!</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
So if i give my pet things with negative mr will it make his charms last longer ? and if so will the differance be worth adding the gear?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
At the bear minimum it will make your recharm on the pet last longer <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If you believe charm is checked every tick then it will help your current charm.
<br />

<br />
If you believe charm is checked once and the duration or the charm is calculated at the time when the charm is landed then ... not for this charm <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
If it makes any difference I personally believe the former over the latter but I do not really want to argue about it ...
<br />

<br />
As for the difference, well that depends on a variety of things not the least of which is the mob you are currently attempting to charm and of course how much -MR you are giving the mob.  Then there is your level relative to the mob whether or not the mob has tash/malo/mala, etc ...
<br />

<br />
At some point the addition of more -MR is simply going to be of limited value, the question is how will you know when you are at that point?  The answer would be to log it, do some experimentation with the mob you wish to learn about and then parse the logs <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Or just do it the lazy way, assume it makes a difference and toss some low cost -MR items on the mob <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
It should also be mentioned that simply because you give a mob an item does not mean it will wear or wield it, as mentioned above.  So it also helps to know whether or not the item is being equipped <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
In general, I would say it is worth it for the mobs I charm.
<br />

<br />
Regards,</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370213" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zanithar TideBreaker</a> - Coercer
<br />
<a href="http://www.therelentless.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Relentless</a>, Cazic Thule
<br />
- Retired -</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
