                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">Basically, whatever class the charmed pet is has NO bearing on its ability to wield weapons.</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"> A charmed cleric pet is more than happy to dual-wield what you give them, as is any other class of pet you can charm</span>
<br />

<br />
For every example that you find of a mob that wields, I can find one of a similar mob not wielding.  It's just not as simple as it is being portrayed.
<br />

<br />
At best, we can say:
<br />

<br />
1. For some creatures, class and race absolutely matter for wielding weapons. For many others, especially higher level ones, it is ignored.
<br />

<br />
2. In some zones and for mobs over a certain level, class does not matter for dual wielding.  In other places being warrior, monk, beastlord, bard, or rogue is a  prerequisite for dual wielding.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">In general though, mostly "humanoid" type NPC's will dual wield. </span>
<br />

<br />
This not a good heuristic any more.  The vast majority of spiders, bugs, goos, wurms, animals, and dragonkin of appropriate level will dual wield.  In Luclin, dual weilding is largely denied to humanoids by class, and in PoP, wielding of any kind is very much determined mob-by-mob.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
